  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Malnutrition or its risk is common among older people. To maintain adequate nutrition,
      increased meal frequency is important. In addition to main meals, regular consumption of
      nutrient- and energy-dense snacks is recommended. The study examines the post-meal responses
      to dairy- and berry-based snacks tailored for older people. The plasma concentrations of
      glucose, insulin and free fatty acids are measured during three hours after snack
      consumption. In addition, subjective satiety responses and heart rate variability are
      recorded.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
